main event: An observer reported a UFO sighting in Dayton, Ohio on April 16, 1968, but the details provided were conflicting and the sighting was captured on an incomplete form.
interesting points: The sighting was marked as conflicting due to differing accounts of course, time, and speed., The report suggests there was confusion regarding the witness's last known sighting date., The observer's account was recorded as part of Project Blue Book, which investigated UFOs from 1947 to 1969., There were multiple forms filled regarding the same phenomena on differing dates that month., The observer's description relied heavily on subsequent incomplete questionnaire responses.
witness description: Observer was likely a civilian who reported the sighting to the Air Force's Project Blue Book.
